whatever the parents have to g=\r\nive.\n\nSimilarly, if you want to get a specific material result, there are s=\r\neveral technicalities to bother about. Even when you bother about them, you=\r\n may not get it right. As I keep emphasizing now and then, there are many c=\r\norruptions in our understanding of the technicalities and the art of gettin=\r\ng specific material results through rituals is nearly extinct. The best app=\r\nroach is to surrender to your deity, use homam or meditation to express you=\r\nr love and surrender and take whatever you are given in return as a prasad.=\r\n Such a person will be favored by deities over the long run.\n\n* * *\n\nNamast=\r\ne Ramakishore,\n\nDifferent points of space and different points of time have=\r\n a different quality to them. Sadhana in Boston is not the same as sadhana =\r\nin Girnar hills or Arunachala hills. Sadhana on a Chauturthi is not the sam=\r\ne as sadhana on Pournima.\n\nIf one is doing a specific sadhana occasionally =\r\n(e.g. a monthly Satya Narayana pooja or a monthly Chandi homam or a monthly=\r\n Krishna homam), it is not a bad idea to pick a day/time that is aligned wi=\r\nth the energy of that deity.\n\nHowever, one can only make so much progress w=\r\nith occasional sadhana. To make real progress and to experience divinity, m=\r\nore intense sadhana is needed. If one is into serious sadhana with a mantra=\r\n/deity, one can do it every day and at all times.\n\n* * *\n\nA lot of beggars =\r\nmay be standing at the gate of a king&#39;s palace, waiting for the king to see=\r\n them when leaving/entering the palace and give them some money. That king =\r\nmay be known to step out of the house to go to a specific place on every so=\r\n and so day and there may be a bigger crowd of beggars gathering at his gat=\r\ne on that day. But, by standing at the gate on that day along with so many =\r\nbeggars, you may or may not be able to get something from the king. On the =\r\nother hand, if you simply stand at the gate everyday, king&#39;s eyes may fall =\r\non you someday!\n\nHave the attitude of a beggar, surrender to the deity, kee=\r\np doing your chosen sadhana everyday and patiently wait for the deity&#39;s gra=\r\nce. That is a sureshot formula for success.\n\n* * *\n\nThe issue of auspicious=\r\n days and times is a double edged sword. While a particular day may be more=\r\n auspicious than other days, it may or may not mean much to one. For exampl=\r\ne, if a particular cricket pitch is easier to bat on, you cannot expect to =\r\ngo there and score a century. International cricketers such as Tendulkar, G=\r\nambhir and Sehwag may score more runs there than at other places, but you m=\r\nay still get out cheaply.\n\nInstead of helping, sadhana done on a particular=\r\nly good day can sometimes bog one down with false pride and expectancy. I r=\r\nemember one incident.\n\nA few years ago, I decided oneday in spring that I w=\r\nanted to spend the coming Saturday meditating with the Gayatri mantra for t=\r\nhe whole day. I got that intention from nowhere and did not look at anythin=\r\ng like tithi, my horoscope etc. I simply decided to go ahead. I mentioned i=\r\nt to Manish and he said, &quot;excellent, go ahead&quot;. I meditated with Gayatri ma=\r\nntra from 5 am till 9:30 pm, getting up only a few times for 2-minute break=\r\ns and having a fistful of saattwik food for lunch in the middle of the day.=\r\n When I finished in the night, I was in a nice state.\n\nNext morning, I real=\r\nized that the previous day was Akshaya Tritiya (Vaisakha Sukla Tritiya, bir=\r\nthday of Ganga and Parasurama and the day Tretayuga started). It is said th=\r\nat spiritual sadhana done on Akshaya Tritiya is 1,000 times more effective =\r\nthan a normal day. I was excited that the day I picked at random happened t=\r\no be an auspicious day.\n\nI mentioned it to Manish. He said, &quot;I knew it was =\r\nAkshaya Tritiya even when you mentioned the intention to me&quot;. I asked him w=\r\nhy he did not tell that to me then. He curtly remarked, &quot;knowing you were d=\r\noing this sadhana on Akshaya Tritiya would not have helped and would have i=\r\nnstead distracted you.&quot;\n\nHe was right. As such, I was a little &quot;proud&quot; of t=\r\nhe sadhana - spending the whole day in japam. There was a bit of excitement=\r\n and expectancy that was present as an undercurrent and somewhat distracted=\r\n my focus on the mantra. Had I known that I was doing it on a day when sadh=\r\nana is supposed to be 1,000 times more effective, that undercurrent of usel=\r\ness excitement would&#39;ve been higher and distracted me even more!\n\nBottomlin=\r\ne: Thumbrules of all kinds exist. But what really matters is the state of y=\r\nour mind. Sometimes, doing a sadhana on an auspicious day can create excite=\r\nment and expectancy and distract one. Doing the same sadhana everyday and p=\r\natiently waiting for it to succeed oneday is perhaps a simpler and more foo=\r\nlproof strategy. My 2 cents..\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n------------ -------=\r\n-- --------- --------- --------- --------- -\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jy=\r\notish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short =\r\nHomam and Pitri Tarpana:\nhttp://www.VedicAst rologer.org\nFilms that make a =\r\ndifference: http://SaraswatiFil ms.org\nSpirituality: http://groups. yahoo.c=\r\nom/ group/vedic- wisdom\nJyotish writings: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/J=\r\nyotishWri tings\n------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- ------=\r\n--- -\n\n---- rajarshi14 &lt;rajarshi14@yahoo. co.in&gt; wrote: \n&gt; \n&gt; Dear Ashutosh=\r\n,\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Someone told me that at the time of homam agnivas is to be\n&gt; &gt; asc=\r\nertained, i.e. it is at prithvi or AkAsh or pAtAl and homam at wrong\n&gt; &gt; ag=\r\nnivas may give adverse results. Is this true? How agnivas can be\n&gt; &gt; ascert=\r\nained/ determined and what are the impacts of 